args:
As the party makes its way through the
mountains to the circus festival, they are
waylaid by thieves. Sensing the danger,
Fritz fights them alone and ends up in
peril. When the party goes to aid him,
they learn about his secret past.
You guys have a real knack for fighting\nthe way Annelie showed you.
Thanks. Although if I'm honest,\nit's a rather tough talent to master.
I understand—but don't fret! We've still\ngot time before the circus festival.
I'm going to train you right up until the\nmoment we arrive, so be ready!
We'll do our best—er, but please try\nnot to be TOO hard on us?
And so, the prince and his friends practiced their\nperformances over and over again...
Until the day they found themselves crossing\nthrough the mountains for the town where the\nfestival was to be held...
You cats are really something.\nI can't believe how quickly you\npicked up all your routines!
Yes, you've all become quite the\nlittle stars, haven't you?
It's just... Well, I know we're trying to\ndisguise ourselves with all this makeup,\nbut I'm not actually sure it's working.
The whole Empire is after us, after all.\nIf word gets out about what we're doing,\nthis troupe will be in grave danger.
We'll cross that road if we come to it.
Remember what I told you before?\nThe show must go on!
And that's no matter what happens,\nso let's keep a positive mindset!
I've got ALL the points! Anyway, when\nyou're up on that stage, nothing matters\nbut the entertainment.

You may be a prince or a scoundrel,
but once the spotlight shines on you,
you're nothing but a performer—
just like the rest of us carnies.
Say, what's wrong, Fritz?\nYou look a little pale there.
Anyway, it's time for us to set up camp.\nI'll take the first patrol.
And I will go with you! It's my duty as\nringmaster to ensure our safety, after all.
No, I got this. You stay.
This isn't something you need to be doing.
I know you're hiding in there, you curs!\nGive it up and come out!
Unless you want me to start in\non some target practice! ...HAH!
Gwar har har! Lookit that dagger fly!\nYer more skilled than ya look, lad!
You chumps're with the thieves guild,\nyeah? Whaddya want with us?
Thieves guild? You wound me, sir!

...Bwaaa ha ha! 'COURSE we want ya!
Buncha circus freaks crossin' a
mountain? Ilia herself couldn't
send a better pack'a marks!
That dagger yer holdin' don't worry me,\nlad—there's a world'a difference between\ntossin' at a target and takin' out a man.
Now make with the cash and valuables\nbefore I get mad and take yer life!
You just don't know when to quit. HAH!
I got more than a couple'a daggers up my\nsleeves, pals—let's see how you like the\npower of my kicks!
Gya! This guy ain't clownin' around!
Oh, I'm no clown, pal. In fact,\nI used to be a thief myself!
Now turn around and beat it before I get\nmad. And if I see you within a mile of\nAnnelie or our people, I'll make you pay.
Bwaaa ha ha! Big talk from guy we got\noutnumbered ten to one!
I have a bad feeling about this.\nWe should search the area.

Didn't I say we had ya outnumbered?
...All right, boys! Take this guy out,
then head for the rest of the circus
and snag whatever ain't nailed down!
I'll never let that happen! HAAAH!
The circus is Annelie's treasure,\nand I ain't letting you hurt it!
I won't let ANYBODY hurt it!
Ah! What are all of you doing here?
Fritz! You're wounded! Why didn't you\nshout for help instead of taking them\nall on by yourself?!
Dammit! Shoulda figured a circus troupe\nwhat runs with a thief'd be home to a\nwhole ring'a brutes!
Thief? What are you talking about?
Bwaaa ha ha ha! Ya don't know?\nYer little dagger boy's a former cutpurse!
Mostlike he's been trickin' all you saps\nwhat so he can make off with the goods.
Ma'am, I didn't... I didn't want you to\nsoil your hands with this bunch.
I know, Fritz. It's all right.
Ya BELIEVE this gutter snake?\nBut he's selling ya the same load'a\nbullplop that we would!
Fritz's past has nothing to do with the\nman he is while up on stage.
He's a proud performer, a colleague...\nand a friend.
What kind of ringmaster would I be if I\ndidn't trust the words of one of my own?
Pfft! I've had enough'a this lovefest.\nGet 'er, boys!
Annelie and Fritz are our colleagues!
And if you want to hurt them,\nyou'll have to deal with us!
Tch... They're tough! Scatter that stuff\nand let's get outta here!
What are they dropping on the ground?\n*sniff* Oh no! Beast blood!
Just wait till the local fiends catch\na whiff'a this! Later, chumps!
Guys! We got fiends comin' in hot!
Right then! Time to work together and\nget ourselves out of this mess.
Don't you start, Fritz! You're family,\nand that's the end of it!
All right, everyone. Let's take out these\nfiends and get off this mountain!
